TEXT 392 128 Left 2 !.tran 0 1.000001m 1m
TEXT -752 -56 Left 2 !.step param run 0 64 1\n.func binary(run,index) floor(run/(2**index))-2*floor(run/(2**(index+1)))\n.func cv(nom,tol,index,pq) if(run==0,nom,if(binary((run-1),index),nom*(1+tol),nom*(1-tol)))\n.func cv2(min,nom,max,index,pq) if(run==0,nom,if(binary((run-1),index),max,min))
TEXT -752 -296 Left 2 ;WCCA simulation creates binnary combinations for each part and it's corner value. \nFunction is named CV - Component value, this function calculates component value. This allows for change of error analysis withouth need to change unerlying schematics.\nDescription of binary fucntion can  be found at https://www.analog.com/en/technical-articles/ltspice-worst-case-circuit-analysis-with-minimal-simulations-runs.html\nFunction was modified so first run is nominal. This  allows op. data label to show nominal value and simplifies data processing.\n# of runs needs to be  set to 2^(# of tolerated components) !\nIndex needs to be adjuster for each independent component
